MOST IMMEDIATE
No. 1/34/1/2013-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 17th June, 2013
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 17th June, 2013:
(i)
the Prime Minister relinquished the charge of (a) the office of the Minister of Road Transport and
Highways; (b) the office of the Minister of Railways; and (c) the office of the Minister of Housing
and Urban Poverty Alleviation;
(ii)
Shri Sis Ram Ola assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Labour and Employment;
(ii)
Shri Mallikarjun Kharge relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Labour and
Employment and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Railways;
Shri Oscar Fernandes assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Road Transport and
Highways;
(iv)
Shri Anand Sharma relinquished the additional charge of the office of the Minister of Textiles.
He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of Commerce and Industry3;
(v)
Dr. Girija Vyas assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Housing and Urban Poverty
Alleviation;
(vi)
(vii)
Dr. Kavuru Samba Siva Rao assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Textiles;
Shri Manikrao Hodlya Gavit assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment;
(vii)
Smt. Santosh Chowdhary assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Health and Family Welfare;
(ix)
(x)
Dr. E.M. Sudarsana Natchiappan assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Commerce and Industry; and
(xi)
Shri Jesudasu Seelam assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of
Finance.
(Sanjukta Ray)
